# SmileSchool Landing Page

Welcome to the **SmileSchool Landing Page** project! This is a responsive, multi-section HTML and CSS website designed as a portfolio and landing page for a fictional online course platform called "SmileSchool." The project demonstrates advanced HTML structure, semantic markup, and modern CSS layout techniques.

## Table of Contents

- [Project Overview](#project-overview)
- [Features](#features)
- [Project Structure](#project-structure)
- [Getting Started](#getting-started)
- [Screenshots](#screenshots)
- [Technologies Used](#technologies-used)
- [Credits](#credits)
- [License](#license)

---

## Project Overview

This project is a static website that showcases the SmileSchool platform, featuring:

- A navigation bar with logo and menu links
- Hero section with a call-to-action
- Instructor highlights
- Testimonial section
- Popular tutorials with ratings
- Free membership benefits
- Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)
- Social media links in the footer

The design is clean, modern, and mobile-friendly.

## Features

- **Responsive Layout:** Adapts to different screen sizes using CSS Flexbox and media queries.
- **Semantic HTML:** Uses proper HTML5 elements for accessibility and SEO.
- **Font Awesome Integration:** Social media and rating icons via CDN.
- **Image Placeholders:** Easily replaceable with your own assets.
- **Multi-section Structure:** Clear separation of content for easy customization.

## Project Structure

```
css_advanced/
  index.html
  README.md
  CSS-Advanced-images/
css_basic/
  base.css
  index.html
  styles.css
  tweets.html
```

- [`css_advanced/index.html`](css_advanced/index.html): Main landing page for SmileSchool.
- [`css_advanced/CSS-Advanced-images/`](css_advanced/CSS-Advanced-images/): Folder for images (add your own assets here).
- [`css_basic/`](css_basic/): Contains a basic portfolio site and shared CSS files.

## Getting Started

1. **Clone the repository** or download the project files.
2. **Open `css_advanced/index.html`** in your web browser to view the landing page.
3. **Add your images** to the `CSS-Advanced-images` folder and update the `src` attributes in the HTML as needed.
4. **Customize content** (text, images, links) to fit your needs.

### Prerequisites

- A modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, Safari)
- No server or build tools required

